HEADWORD: Monodynamism
<hw>Mon`o*dy"na*mism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The theory
that the various forms of activity in nature are manifestations of the
same force.</def> <rj><au>G. H. Lewes.</au></rj> <note>A philosophical
form of the grand unified theory?</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

